<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,999,1385]" pageId="6" pageNumber="457">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,444,1179,1205]" pageId="6" pageNumber="457">Distributional notes.</emphasis>
The eastern end of the distribution of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Esper, [1805])" baseAuthorityName="Esper" baseAuthorityYear="1805" box="[879,1149,1178,1206]" class="Insecta" family="Pieridae" genus="Colias" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="457" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="erate">
<emphasis box="[879,970,1180,1206]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="457">C. erate</emphasis>
(Esper, [1805])
</taxonomicName>
in Tibetan limit seems to be at Jilong, SC. Tibet. A few specimens of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Esper" baseAuthorityYear="1805" box="[654,746,1216,1242]" class="Insecta" family="Pieridae" genus="Colias" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="457" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="erate">
<emphasis box="[654,746,1216,1242]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="457">C. erate</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were collected by the senior author from a locality at Jilong Town (
<geoCoordinate box="[230,346,1251,1277]" degrees="28.3937" direction="north" orientation="latitude" pageId="6" pageNumber="457" precision="5" value="28.3937">28.3937N</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate box="[358,471,1251,1278]" degrees="85.3602" direction="east" orientation="longitude" pageId="6" pageNumber="457" precision="5" value="85.3602">85.3602E</geoCoordinate>
), with male upper side borders not spotted. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Motschulsky" authorityYear="1861" box="[965,1147,1251,1278]" class="Insecta" family="Pieridae" genus="Colias" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="457" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="poliographus">
<emphasis box="[965,1147,1251,1278]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="457">C. poliographus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is commonly seen in SE. Tibet. But no specimen of either species has been collected from the areas of Nielamu, Yadong and Cuona. In the Himalayan areas, 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Esper" baseAuthorityYear="1805" box="[357,450,1324,1350]" class="Insecta" family="Pieridae" genus="Colias" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="457" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="erate">
<emphasis box="[357,450,1324,1350]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="457">C. erate</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is recorded from 
<collectingCountry box="[657,724,1323,1349]" name="Nepal" pageId="6" pageNumber="457">Nepal</collectingCountry>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Motschulsky" authorityYear="1861" box="[782,966,1323,1350]" class="Insecta" family="Pieridae" genus="Colias" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="457" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="poliographus">
<emphasis box="[782,966,1323,1350]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="457">C. poliographus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from E. 
<collectingCountry box="[1072,1153,1323,1349]" name="Bhutan" pageId="6" pageNumber="457">Bhutan</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Grieshuber, J. &amp; Worthy, R. &amp; Lamas, G." box="[1170,1432,1323,1349]" pageId="6" pageNumber="457" refId="ref15180" refString="Grieshuber, J., Worthy, R. &amp; Lamas, G. (2012) The genus Colias Fabricius, 1807. Jan Haugum's annotated catalogue of the Old World Colias. Tshikolovets Publications, Pardubice, 438 pp." type="book" year="2012">
Grieshuber 
<emphasis box="[1305,1364,1323,1349]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="457">et al.</emphasis>
2012
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Grieshuber, J" box="[151,344,1359,1385]" pageId="6" pageNumber="457" refId="ref14730" refString="Grieshuber, J (2014) Guide to the butterflies of the Palearctic region. Pieridae Part II. Omnes Artes, Milano, 86 pp." type="book" year="2014">Grieshuber 2014</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
